  "text": "Direct Numerical Simulations (DNS) of turbulent flows is a very important research tool, utilized across a range of scientific communities [CITATION_1] . DNS is used extensively to validate statistical models, and to further our understanding of complex mechanisms taking place inside turbulent flows. One of the many advantages of DNS is that it provides all information about a flow, and quantities that can be very hard to study experimentally, like velocity-pressure interactions, are trivially extracted from a DNS. In this regard, DNS both complements and extends the knowledge we are able to extract from experiments.",
